'''Rashh''' was a rebellious [[Transport/Legends|transport]] [[Captain/Legends|captain]] who had dealings with [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Darrin Arkanian]]. After Arkanian had rescued his [[Padawan/Legends|apprentice]], [[Corwin Shelvay/Legends|Corwin Shelvay]], from [[High Inquisitor]] [[Antinnis Tremayne|Tremayne]], the pair attempted to rendezvous with Rashh to escape [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]]. Tremayne intercepted them before they could meet with Rassh, however, and killed Arkanian. Shelvay was able to defeat the High Inquisitor and escape.<ref name="Dark Vendetta">{{GalaxyCite|8|Dark Vendetta (short story)}}</ref>

By 37 [[Great ReSynchronization|GrS]], Rashh had become a captain of a [[Bulk freighter/Legends|bulk freighter]]. He modified five [["Hatchling" maintenance droid|Hatchling]] [[Maintenance droid/Legends|maintenance droids]], replacing one tool hardpoint with a high-powered [[Blaster/Legends|blaster]] unit, allowing them to serve as both repair and security droids. He regarded them as a cost-effective and versatile droid, and reported this opinion in version 4.7.1 of [[Cynabar's Droid Datalog]].<ref name="CFTD">''[[Cynabar's Fantastic Technology: Droids]]''</ref>

